        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 11:25AM EDT by NWS Charleston SC</headline>
        <description>At 1125 AM EDT, Public reported a strong thunderstorm over Beaufort,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Public reported.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Beaufort, Port Royal, Ladys Island, Beaufort Marine Corps Air
Station, Burton, Parris Island, Shell Point, Beaufort County
Airport, McTeer Memorial Bridge and Beaufort Memorial Hospital.
</description>
        <instruction>Stay tuned to NOAA Weather Radio All Hazards, TV or your local news
source for the latest information from the National Weather Service.

If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
